Dialogue: Well, that’s not really how it works, Siobhan. We would have to
handle that sort of pivot very delicately.
Uh-huh. As I say, it’s a complex situation so …
Just ranking the facilities. Still on the look-out for my dream
prison.
Oh, sure. But if it does I’m leaning towards
No, Shiv. No. Cumberland is the prison camp in Maryland.
Otisville is Orange County. The Jewish jail?
Just hearing a lot of good things. Kosher vending machines.
Sturdy bunks. No pool, but still.
Apparently they’re calling me Terminal Tom, down on seven,
because I’ve got ‘cancer of the career’.
Ravenhead has his own battalions. He – values his
independence.
Well he’s not going to like it.
I mean, I’ll do it.
But. Just in terms of – you know, of corporate governance and
optics, and – I probably shouldn’t take – like orders from you.
Much. Because of corporate governance.
Yeah and in terms of the org chart. And my … masculinity?
But it undermines me if I look at the wall and the organizational
chart suggests, ‘You are being fucked in the ass by your wife.’
No sure.
But really it is?
Okay. Sure. I’ll speak to him.
Knock knock. Is this the home of my distant assistant?!
Terminal Tom calling. The ghost at the feast. The shame
sponge.
Uh-huh, yeah, just got my clock cleaned by Ravenhead.
Chewed me the fuck out. It’s cool. It’s just the job. I only
mention to amuse.
Yeah. And now I’m down here to apply the thumbscrews. Ooh,
courtesy pastries.
Correct.
Delicious, carby, carrots.
Big fucking stick. So?
Good. Greg, honestly, you can probably ask for whatever you
want.
Yeah well, you’re an asset now. And I’ll have to eat it and like it.
Go on, what do you want?
Greg, why did I never talk to you before, you’re like a real
person with your own little insights and opinions! Okay, let’s
game this—
Ray’s an asshole. But maybe hands-on to start …
Right. I guess you’ve already got it gamed?
Heh. Ha!
An amusing notion has occurred to me, Greg!
Yes. You’re going to be running a theme park and here’s me,
going to prison. You’re going to be living in a magical castle
while I’m going to be down in a dungeon, sucking off ogres for
phone cards.
Greg – what do you know about Nero and Sporus?
Sporus, Greg. He was a young slave boy. Nero’s favorite. You
know what he did to him?
Nero pushed his wife down the stairs then he had Sporus
castrated and he married him instead. He gave him a ring and
made him dress up like his dead wife.
I bought a book on the Romans, to read in prison. It’s a big
book.
It’s a decent book. I’d castrate you and marry you in a
heartbeat.
See if you can pull me to the ground, Greg! Let’s fight like
chickens! Let’s have a punching match.
Come on, come at me! Fight me like a rooster, you weakling.
Why are you such a cuck, Greg?
‘I don’t want to, I don’t want to.’ I don’t want to either, Greg. It
was a joke, you idiot. Dude, you are so hard to riff with. Big
career obstacle for you there. Big.
Hey, yeah, so it’s a no from Ravenhead. He just doesn’t see
how he can accommodate the pivot.
Yeah he was quite unpleasant about it all.
Uh-huh. That’s my level. ‘Tom Wambsgans, minion wrangler
and shit-eater.’
I just keep thinking about, when we get home and before dinner
we have that first glass of cold white wine? On an empty
stomach, that very cold glass of wine – I just fucking love that.
So I did some research and I got deep into the prison blogs
again – about ‘toilet wine’, but then I got worried I’d forget to
‘burp’ my bag of ‘ketchup hooch’ and it would explode.
But the truth is, I’m not going to get wine, of any temperature, in
prison. There’s no fine wines in prison, Shiv.
You don’t get to choose what you eat in prison and you don’t
get to say what you do in prison. And like how late can you
read? When is lights-out?
I’m fucking terrified, Shiv.
Uh-huh. Sure, I know.
But what if it isn’t? What if I buckle?
You said it was a money pit?
Uh-huh sure. Sure.
